pageDescription: Bot Filters are functions that are useful for filtering bots.

comment.shortText: Creates a bot filter that includes bots that are in the given dimension and at the given X and Y position.
comment.text: When this filter is used with [`getBots(...filters)`](ref:getbots-filters), the returned bots are sorted in the same order that they are stacked. This means that the first bot in the array is at the bottom of the stack and the last bot is at the top of the stack (assuming they're stackable).

tags.text:
Find all the bots at (1, 2) in the "test" dimension.
let bots = getBots(atPosition("test", 1, 2));

comment.shortText: the name of the dimension.
the X position. That is, the left-right position of the bots in the dimension.
the Y position. That is, the forward-backward position of the bots in the dimension.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots that are in the given dimension and at the given X and Y position.

comment.shortText:
Creates a bot filter that includes bots created by the given bot.
That is, they have [`#creator`](tags:creator) set to the [`#id`](tags:id) of the given bot.
comment.text: > This function behaves exactly like `byTag("creator", getID(bot))`.

tags.text:
Find all the bots created by this bot.
let bots = getBots(byCreator(thisBot));

comment.shortText: the bot that created the other bots.

comment.shortText: Creates a bot filter that includes bots that have the given tag that matches the given value.

tags.text:
Find all the bots with #name set to "bob".
let bots = getBots(byTag("#name", "bob"));

Find all bots with a height larger than 2.
let bots = getBots(byTag("#height", height => height > 2));

Find all bots with the "test" tag.
let bots = getBots(byTag("#test"));
Bot Filters are functions that are useful for filtering bots.

comment.shortText: the name of the tag. Bots that have this tag will be included as long as they also match the second parameter.

the value that the tag should match. If not specified, then all bots with the tag will be included. If specified, then only bots that have the same tag value will be included. If you specify a function as the value, then it will be used to match tag values.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots that have the given tag that matches the given value.

tags.text:
Find all the bots with #name set to "bob".
let bots = getBots(byTag("#name", "bob"));

Find all bots with a height larger than 2.
let bots = getBots(byTag("#height", height => height > 2));

Find all bots with the "test" tag.
let bots = getBots(byTag("#test"));
Bot Filters are functions that are useful for filtering bots.

comment.shortText: Creates a bot filter that includes bots which match any (i.e. one or more) of the given filters.
the filters that should be used.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots which match any (i.e. one or more) of the given filters.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots that are in the given dimension. That is, they have the given tag set to true.
comment.text: > This function behaves exactly like [`byTag(tag, filter)`](ref:byTag) with the `value` parameter set to `true`.
comment.returns: A function that returns true if the given bot is in the dimension and false if it is not.

tags.text:
Find all the bots in the "test" dimension.
let bots = getBots(inDimension("test"));

comment.shortText: the name of the dimension.

comment.shortText: Creates a bot filter that includes bots in the same stack as the given bot. The given bot will always be included by this filter as long the given bot is in the given dimension.
comment.text: When this filter is used with [`getBots(...filters)`](ref:getbots-filters), the returned bots are sorted in the same order that they are stacked. This means that the first bot in the array is at the bottom of the stack and the last bot is at the top of the stack (assuming they're stackable).

tags.text:
Find all bots in the same stack as thisBot in the "test" dimension.
let bots = getBots(inStack(this, "test"));

comment.shortText: the bot that other bots should be in the same stack with.
the name of the dimension.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots in the same stack as the given bot. The given bot will always be included by this filter as long the given bot is in the given dimension.

comment.shortText: Creates a bot filter that includes bots which are neighboring the given bot. Optionally takes a direction that the neighboring bots must be in.

tags.text:
Find all bots in front of this bot in the test dimension.
const bots = getBots(neighboring(this, "test", "front"));

Find all bots around this bot in the test dimension.
const bots = getBots(neighboring(this, "test"));

comment.shortText: the bot that the other bots need to be neighboring.
the dimension that the other bots need to be in.

the neighboring direction to check. If not specified, then all of the supported directions will be checked. Currently, the supported directions are front, right, back, and left. If an unsupported direction is specified, then no bots will be included.
Creates a bot filter that includes bots which are neighboring the given bot. Optionally takes a direction that the neighboring bots must be in.

tags.text:

comment.shortText: Creates a function that includes bots which _do not_ match the given filter.

tags.text:
Find all bots that are not in the test dimension
const bots = getBots(not(inDimension("test")));

comment.shortText: the bot filter whose results should be negated.
Creates a function that includes bots which _do not_ match the given filter.

tags.text:
